ygData.messageBody:
Count me among the crew Harm, sir! That hammerhead in Lake Rathe is still
way red to me! I've always been pessimistic about Elitists sir! Err, no
I've always been elitist about Pessimists... err, ummm... Well, you know
what I mean. Heh got killed by a warp. I was testing Lullaby and wanted to
kill my test subjects. The wolf warped over to the zone and I forgot about
it, until...

"I hate bard's like you!"
Holly Windstalker slashes you for 60
Holly Windstalker slashes you for 60
Cros Trewind casts a spell
You are burned
You are stunned...

Loading, Please Wait...

Sigh, can't even test a bug without getting killed by another one.

Your chum Kit
Nooooooooooooooooooooooooo... <splash>

-----Original Message-----
From: Ryan Honeyman [mailto:honeyman@...]
Sent: Monday, January 31, 2000 10:41 AM
To: 'eqbards@onelist.com'
Subject: RE: [eqbards] (OT) Lower level discrimination was Play Time?


From: Ryan Honeyman <honeyman@...>

> Not sure I'm even fit to be a Cabin Boy on the Mighty Rokenn's ship
though.
> Hey what was all that claptrap about Instill Doubt making ships go faster?
> Was that another of Capt. Rokenn's inventions gone awry? That has to be
the
> silliest patch message piece I have seen yet!

See Steven K., I'm not so bitter after all now I am. ;-)

I'm just saying the game was cool and now it sucks big pointy Cazics,
that's all. ;p Oh, and now instead of a blocky hill giant warping
on top me, a pretty multitextured, high polycount, antialaised giant
will be warping on top of me ;)

As for you Kit, Capt Rokenn doesn't believe in half measures!
You can either join our ranks of elitest pessimists and bash
Verant or you can 'Walk the plank!'

Harmonic, aye aye kiptin.
